intro: Farsetia ellenbeckii, commonly known as the Ellenbeck's farsetia, is a species of flowering plant in the family Apiaceae. It is native to South Africa and is characterized by its slender, branched stems and small, greenish-yellow flowers. The plant typically grows in rocky or sandy soils and is adapted to arid or semi-arid environments. It has pinnately divided leaves and produces small, dry fruits known as schizocarps. Farsetia ellenbeckii is often found in open habitats such as grasslands and rocky outcrops.
